{
  "stem": "19969.7",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 13.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[DRINKS] Then a Japanese crew came in about two or three years ago also.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[COUGHS] They were trying to-- there was a Japanese battalion that claimed they liberated Dachau, an artillery battalion.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Well, in the first place, artillery battalions don't go around liberating anything, they follow up.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But they claimed to have liberated Dachau and they claimed that they were told that they couldn't tell anybody that they had- oh, it appeared in the newspapers on the west coast.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They had a big reunion in San Francisco.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And one of these guys, this Japanese soldier, said-- they were American soldiers, but they were of Japanese ancestry.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Well, he met with Cardinal Niemoller-- and Niemoller wasn't even there-- and how they rescued all these people.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They weren't there at all.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It's true they were in another corps, which was off on the right that was headed towards Austria.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "What they ran into was this group that was being marched out of Dachau, see.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Anyway, they-- the crew was here to try to establish and I disabused them of that in a hurry, I think.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But they put out a film on it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They sent me a copy of it, but I-- it won't fit in my thing in here.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But they gave me this watch.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "[LAUGHING] It's a Japanese watch I've never heard of, but it's been running good ever since anyway.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We did that in the backyard out here in the summertime.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the only thing I can tell future generations is to try to eliminate hatred and prejudice and intolerance for various groups and various races and various religions.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Let everybody live their own life, that's my message.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And respect the religion or other race.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
